      • existBorderRouter

        public boolean existBorderRouter​(java.lang.String borderRouterIp)
        Check if a border router IP is exist, notice that this method doesn't check if the IP is in database, it checks if the router IP exists in the real network. In this dummy implementation, return true for the probability of 0.8, return false otherwise.
        Specified by:
        existBorderRouter in class AbstractAccessBorderRouterService
        Parameters:

      • getSensorIpByBorderRouterIp

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getSensorIpByBorderRouterIp​(java.lang.String borderRouterIp)
        Take as input a String of borderRouterIp, return a list of IPv6 address of sensors that are connected to the given border router. If the input borderRouterIp is inValid, return null instead. This method just create dummy sensor ip for each input borde router. The number of sensor will be a random number from 0 to 6.
        Specified by:
        getSensorIpByBorderRouterIp in class AbstractAccessBorderRouterService
        Parameters:
        borderRouterIp - The IPv6 address of border router you want to query.
        Returns:
        A list of sensor IPv6 address.
